# Ablation 2 — Qwen2.5-Coder-3B Coordination Collapse Study

## Complete Report

---

## 1. Overview & Objective

This experiment is a **cross-family ablation** of a broader research project studying **coordination collapse in multi-agent code generation pipelines**. The main study used **DeepSeek** models (1.3B for Architect + Implementer, 6.7B for Validator). This ablation replaces all models with a single **Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-3B-Instruct** model for all three agent roles (Architect, Implementer, Validator), testing whether the coordination collapse phenomenon is model-family dependent or architectural.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Central research question:** Does coordination collapse persist when switching from DeepSeek to Qwen? If so, this confirms collapse is an **architectural** issue of multi-agent pipelines, not a model-specific limitation.

---

## 2. Experimental Setup

### 2.1 Model
- **Model:** `Qwen/Qwen2.5-Coder-3B-Instruct`
- **Precision:** `float16`
- **Device:** CUDA (GPU)
- **Same model for ALL 3 roles** — Architect, Implementer, and Validator

### 2.2 Dataset
- **HumanEval** (OpenAI) — 164 coding tasks
- Evaluation via `run_test_safe()` — subprocess-based test execution with 10-second timeout

### 2.3 Pipeline Configurations

| System | Description | Agent Flow |
|--------|-------------|------------|
| **Single-Agent (SA)** | Direct code generation from prompt | Prompt → Code → Test |
| **2-Agent Pipeline** | Architect creates spec, Implementer codes from spec | Prompt → Architect Spec → Implementer Code → Test |
| **3-Agent Pipeline** | Adds Validator + revision loop | Prompt → Architect Spec → Implementer Code v1 → Structural Pre-check + LLM Validator → (optional) Implementer Revision → Code Final → Test |

### 2.4 Token Budgets

| Role | Max Tokens |
|------|-----------|
| Architect | 512 |
| Implementer | 384 |
| Validator | 256 |
| Implementer (revision) | 400 |

### 2.5 Reproducibility
- **Seed:** 42 (Python `random`, NumPy, PyTorch)
- **Greedy decoding** (`do_sample=False`)
- **Run on Google Colab** with CUDA GPU

