## 9. Recovery Breakdown (3-Agent)

| Metric | Count |
|--------|-------|
| Total validator-triggered cases | 77 |
| Recovered by revision | 21 |
| Still failing after revision | 56 |

### Why Recovery Fails (56 unrecovered cases):

| Reason | Count |
|--------|-------|
| Spec has any defect | 41 |
| - Empty function signature | 40 |
| - Missing/empty constraints | 1 |
| - Truncated spec | 1 |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Root cause:** The Implementer receives violation feedback + the **same defective spec**. Violation descriptions cannot compensate for information that was never in the spec. Revision can fix code bugs — it cannot fill information gaps from the Architect.
>
> **This mechanistically explains the detection-remediation gap:**
> - **Detection (Validator):** Works — flags structurally wrong code
> - **Remediation (Implementer):** Fails — the spec is the bottleneck, not the code

